definitions.definition: The dried, wrinkled fruit of certain species of plum.
An old woman, especially a wrinkly one.
To become wrinkled like a dried plum, as the fingers and toes do when kept submerged in water.
To remove excess material from a tree or shrub; to trim, especially to make more healthy or productive.
definitions.example: A good grape grower will prune the vines once a year.

definitions.definition: To cut down or shorten (by the removal of unnecessary material).
definitions.example: to prune a budget, or an essay

definitions.definition: To remove unnecessary branches from a tree data structure.
To preen; to prepare; to dress.
